5-10% high-end calls. 60-70% workhorse calls. All within Cursor Pro.

## Token Rules
- Select model in Cursor picker before each session — don't leave on expensive default
- High-end for thinking. Workhorse for doing.
- Cmd+K + Haiku = no chat context cost
- @ mention 2-3 files max
- .cursorrules = free instructions
- 7-day cut rule on failing bets

## Build Loop
1. PLAN — Opus 4.8 / Fable 5 (Cursor chat, high-end model selected)
2. SCAFFOLD — Composer Auto (Cursor built-in)
3. BUILD — Haiku 4.5 Cmd+K + Luna (workhorse selected)
4. DECIDE — Opus 4.8 if blocked (high-end, 0-2 calls)
5. TEST — no AI
6. VERIFY — Sonnet 5 (high-end)
7. FINALIZE — document, cut or continue

## Stack Defaults (product infra, separate from Cursor Pro)
- Next.js 14+, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, Supabase, Stripe, Vercel
- AU dates DD/MM/YYYY, currency AUD, timezone Australia/Sydney

## Portfolio Rules
- 50-55 bets, 1-2 winners expected (2.5% rule)
- 7-day cut rule | Friday review | Document in /reports/
